      "role": "user",
      "content": "but isn't that just a slippery slope? if we say religious conscience is a \"core value\" that justifies breaking general laws, doesn't that basically give religious groups a \"get out of jail free\" card for anything they want? if a group says a certain labor law or healthcare mandate goes against their faith, shouldn't the secular laws of the land take precedence to ensure everyone is treated equally? it seems like you're implying that religious rights are inherently more fundamental than civil rights or equality under the law.",
